WEBVTT

00:00:00.090 --> 00:00:02.280
Today, I'm going to show you an incredible time

00:00:02.280 --> 00:00:04.590
saver that you may have never noticed in your

00:00:04.590 --> 00:00:08.400
canvas course, it's the link validation tool. Got

00:00:08.400 --> 00:00:11.640
any links in your course? Of course you do. Maybe

00:00:11.640 --> 00:00:14.100
you've got a link to a canvas guide, or you're

00:00:14.100 --> 00:00:17.190
linking students from a content page to a

00:00:17.190 --> 00:00:21.180
discussion or web resource. Plus, unbeknownst to

00:00:21.180 --> 00:00:24.990
many instructors, images on a canvas page are not

00:00:24.990 --> 00:00:28.170
actually embedded on the page. They're actually

00:00:28.500 --> 00:00:32.310
HTML code linking back to the specific image in

00:00:32.310 --> 00:00:35.310
the files area. Your course is likely full of

00:00:35.310 --> 00:00:39.330
links, and we all know links break. The good news

00:00:39.330 --> 00:00:41.820
is you don't have to go through every page in your

00:00:41.820 --> 00:00:45.030
course every semester double checking that all

00:00:45.030 --> 00:00:48.000
your links work, because canvas will do it for you

00:00:48.270 --> 00:00:50.490
after you've imported your content into the new

00:00:50.490 --> 00:00:53.370
semester's teaching shell. But before you publish

00:00:53.370 --> 00:00:56.640
the course, you'll want to use the Validate Links

00:00:56.640 --> 00:00:59.850
in Content tool. Let me show you what it looks

00:00:59.850 --> 00:01:03.210
like in a course. To find the Validate Links tool,

00:01:03.330 --> 00:01:06.630
click settings. In the course navigation, select

00:01:06.630 --> 00:01:09.990
the Validate Links in Content option in the right

00:01:09.990 --> 00:01:13.530
menu bar. Then click the Start Link Validation

00:01:13.530 --> 00:01:17.190
button. The tool will scan your entire course and

00:01:17.190 --> 00:01:20.010
give you a report that shows which links don't

00:01:20.010 --> 00:01:22.440
appear to be working, where they're located in the

00:01:22.440 --> 00:01:25.410
course, and what the issue likely is. Let's talk

00:01:25.410 --> 00:01:28.710
about deciphering the report results. This first

00:01:28.710 --> 00:01:32.160
error tells me there is deleted content on the

00:01:32.160 --> 00:01:34.770
Meet Your Classmates discussion page, and the

00:01:34.770 --> 00:01:38.790
error itself shows as this download link with an

00:01:38.790 --> 00:01:41.730
image icon that invariably means the image on the

00:01:41.730 --> 00:01:44.820
page isn't displaying properly. To check, I'll

00:01:44.820 --> 00:01:47.820
right click on the title of the page. I like to

00:01:47.820 --> 00:01:50.970
open things in a new tab so I don't lose my place

00:01:50.970 --> 00:01:54.090
in this link validator page. When I go to the Meet

00:01:54.090 --> 00:01:56.820
Your Classmates discussion, sure enough, the

00:01:56.820 --> 00:01:59.580
banner isn't displaying. To remedy it, I can

00:01:59.580 --> 00:02:03.000
simply re-import the image properly. I'll make

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:05.190
sure it has appropriate alt text.

00:02:07.960 --> 00:02:12.070
And then save the page. The next error indicates

00:02:12.070 --> 00:02:15.580
non-existent content. This typically means the

00:02:15.580 --> 00:02:18.220
link is going to a page in your course that no

00:02:18.220 --> 00:02:21.520
longer exists. Usually because you change the page

00:02:21.520 --> 00:02:25.030
title after creating the link to fix that. Open

00:02:25.030 --> 00:02:28.270
the editor on the problem page and I'm just going

00:02:28.270 --> 00:02:32.120
to check. Yes, indeed. It's telling me the page

00:02:32.120 --> 00:02:35.480
does not exist. So I can go back here and as

00:02:35.480 --> 00:02:41.000
before, will simply relink. By first removing the

00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:44.750
bad link, highlighting the descriptive link text

00:02:45.050 --> 00:02:48.680
and then choosing coarse links, finding the

00:02:48.680 --> 00:02:51.860
correct page or whatever it is you are linking to

00:02:52.070 --> 00:02:55.220
and then saving the page. The learning links page

00:02:55.220 --> 00:02:58.490
has two errors. This first tells us a link is

00:02:58.490 --> 00:03:01.400
going to a different course. That might happen

00:03:01.400 --> 00:03:04.100
when you import content from another course or a

00:03:04.100 --> 00:03:07.040
previous semester. Shell. Typically, the links get

00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:10.130
updated during the import process, but if the link

00:03:10.130 --> 00:03:13.010
wasn't embedded correctly, it may still lead back

00:03:13.010 --> 00:03:15.980
to the previous course. You'll still see it

00:03:16.220 --> 00:03:18.350
because you're in both courses, but it will be a

00:03:18.350 --> 00:03:20.900
problem for your current students since they're

00:03:20.900 --> 00:03:23.390
not likely to be enrolled in the other course.

00:03:23.390 --> 00:03:26.990
Shell. If I go to the page and click the link, it

00:03:26.990 --> 00:03:29.570
looks fine to me, but here's how to tell it's a

00:03:29.570 --> 00:03:34.190
problem up here in the U. RL, it identifies the

00:03:34.190 --> 00:03:39.920
course as 28409. When I go back to the original

00:03:39.920 --> 00:03:43.100
page, the learning links page, it tells me I'm in

00:03:43.100 --> 00:03:48.770
course 28541 whoops different course. So to fix it,

00:03:48.860 --> 00:03:52.430
just as we did before, you'll remove the offending

00:03:52.430 --> 00:03:55.760
link and re link it to the correct page in this

00:03:55.880 --> 00:03:59.750
course shell. The other link says external links

00:03:59.750 --> 00:04:02.900
were unreachable. Canvas is a secure environment,

00:04:02.900 --> 00:04:05.360
meaning you have to log in to access it, and it

00:04:05.360 --> 00:04:09.110
doesn't like taking students outside of canvas. So

00:04:09.110 --> 00:04:12.560
this error will show up with links leading to an

00:04:12.560 --> 00:04:15.920
external web site. The link may or may not

00:04:15.920 --> 00:04:18.530
actually be broken, but you'll want to confirm

00:04:18.530 --> 00:04:21.230
that. So again go to the page. We're going to look

00:04:21.230 --> 00:04:24.740
for case studies of real scientific experiments

00:04:24.890 --> 00:04:29.840
when I click it. Yes, indeed. This is a broken

00:04:29.840 --> 00:04:33.530
page on that external website. To correct it. I'd

00:04:33.530 --> 00:04:36.470
have to do a little detective work to find either

00:04:36.470 --> 00:04:40.190
the correct page on this website, or a new webpage

00:04:40.280 --> 00:04:43.040
that gives students the content I want. And then

00:04:43.040 --> 00:04:45.980
on the Learning Links page I would relink this to

00:04:45.980 --> 00:04:49.070
the correct page. You'll notice right above here

00:04:49.070 --> 00:04:52.850
there's another external link on the page to which

00:04:52.850 --> 00:04:56.120
the link validator did not give us an unreachable

00:04:56.120 --> 00:04:58.640
error. I don't know why that happens, but it does

00:04:58.640 --> 00:05:02.480
sometimes. In any case, if we had gotten an

00:05:02.480 --> 00:05:06.170
unreachable error on this Virtual Labs link again,

00:05:06.170 --> 00:05:10.130
we'll click it just to see. And this time it's not

00:05:10.130 --> 00:05:13.070
actually a broken link. So that means I could

00:05:13.070 --> 00:05:16.700
ignore that particular alert in the validate links

00:05:16.700 --> 00:05:20.060
list. You never know when the unreachable error is

00:05:20.060 --> 00:05:23.390
a false positive or not, so it's best to always

00:05:23.390 --> 00:05:26.570
check the destination link by clicking on it and

00:05:26.570 --> 00:05:29.780
seeing if it's actually going to the website, or

00:05:29.780 --> 00:05:32.420
if the page is broken. As long as I make sure the

00:05:32.420 --> 00:05:35.360
link is at working, I can ignore that error in the

00:05:35.360 --> 00:05:38.990
report. The next error is telling me I've got

00:05:38.990 --> 00:05:42.020
links leading to unpublished content. That's a

00:05:42.020 --> 00:05:44.550
good thing to know because it may be intentional.

00:05:44.570 --> 00:05:47.270
I don't want students accessing these pages yet,

00:05:47.600 --> 00:05:50.990
or it may be an oversight. I can easily corrected

00:05:51.140 --> 00:05:54.320
by going to the unpublished item and publishing it.

00:05:54.530 --> 00:05:57.440
Once you've fixed all the errors, run the link

00:05:57.440 --> 00:06:00.830
validator again to double check if you had

00:06:00.830 --> 00:06:04.040
external links that were a false positive before,

00:06:04.050 --> 00:06:06.680
those may show up again, but you've checked them

00:06:06.680 --> 00:06:09.320
so you know you can ignore those alerts. Another

00:06:09.320 --> 00:06:13.040
odd thing is sometimes, as happened here, new

00:06:13.040 --> 00:06:15.650
errors will show up when I rerun the link

00:06:15.650 --> 00:06:18.710
validator. I have no idea why that happens, but

00:06:18.710 --> 00:06:21.650
just know that it might. So this error did not

00:06:21.650 --> 00:06:24.590
show before, but it's showing now. Just make the

00:06:24.590 --> 00:06:27.860
corrections to the new alerts as necessary. To sum

00:06:27.860 --> 00:06:30.230
it up, the Link Validation tool is a really

00:06:30.230 --> 00:06:32.360
convenient way to make sure you're not sending

00:06:32.360 --> 00:06:33.830
students to broken links.
